&lt;li&gt;Birhanu Eshete&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PoisonSpot focuses on precise detection of clean-label backdoor attacks by tracking how individual training samples affect parameter updates over time. The system attributes poisoning influence through provenance lineage and flags high-risk samples for rejection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;what-this-project-delivers&#34;&gt;What This Project Delivers&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fine-grained training provenance capture inspired by dynamic taint tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sample-level poisoning attribution to detect stealthy clean-label attacks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Artifact package for reproducible benchmarking under adaptive threat models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
